Neighborhood: The Villages Of Palm Beach Lakes

Company Description: Founded IN 1930, Publix Super Markets Is One Of The Largest Supermarket Chains IN The United States. The Company Specializes IN A Variety Of Grocery Products, Such As Meat, Seafood, Dairy Items, And Natural And Organic Foods. It Operates Deli, Bakery And Produce Departments. Its Pharmacy Division Offers Medical Screenings And Insurance Services. The Retailer Also Provides Cakes And Desserts For Weddings And Special Occasions. IN Addition, Publix Super Markets Organizes Cooking Classes. It Operates A Food And Nutrition Center That Offers Information On Health, Recipes And Weight Management. The Retailer S Additional Services Include Gift Cards And Film Development. It Publishes A Magazine That Features Articles On Food And Nutrition. With A Presence IN West Palm Beach, Fla., Publix Super Markets Also Operates Distribution Centers And Manufacturing Facilities.

Founded IN 1930, Publix Super Markets Is One Of The Largest, Employee-Owned Supermarket Chains IN The United States. With Annual Sales Of More Than $23.9 Billion, It Has A Staff Of Over 140,000 Employees. The Chain Maintains Nearly 1,000 Supermarkets IN South Carolina, Alabama And Tennessee. Publix Super Markets Has Distribution Centers Throughout Florida And Georgia. It Has Received The Diversistar Award For Excelling IN Promoting Workplace Diversity Practices. The Chain S Supermarkets Specialize IN A Variety Of Grocery Products, Such As Seafood, Dairy, And Natural And Organic Food Items. Its Supermarkets Operate Deli, Bakery And Produce Departments. Publix Super Markets  Supermarkets Have Pharmacy Divisions That Provide Medical Screenings And Insurance Services. Its Supermarkets Offer Cakes And Desserts For Weddings, Baby Showers And Anniversaries, As Well As Sell Gift Cards Of Various Denominations That Can Be Redeemed At Any Of Its Locations. Publix Super Markets Publishes The Publix Baby Club, Publix Preschool Pals, Publix Familystyle, And Publix Greenwise Market Magazines. It Operates Publix Pharmacy, Which Provides Prescriptions At More Than 700 Pharmacies Throughout Alabama, Florida And Georgia

Publix Super Market Has Grown Into A Fortune 500 Company With More Than 870 Stores. The Grocery Store Chain Is One Of The Fastest-Growing, Employee-Owned Companies IN The United States. Also Known As One Of The 10 Largest-Volume Supermarket Chains IN The Nation, The Company S Retail Sales Reached Nearly $20 Billion IN 2004. Publix Offers Pharmacy And Photo Development Services Along With Food And Other Grocery Store Items. A Privately Held Company Operating Stores IN Florida, Georgia, South Carolina, Alabama And Tennessee, George W. Jenkins Founded Publix IN Winter Haven, Fla., IN 1930. Publix Super Market Maintains A Location IN Weston, Fla.
